write a Python program to print out the first 100 prime numbers
def is_prime(n): 
    if n <= 1: return False # no primes below 2!  
    for i in range(2, int(n**0.5)+1): if (n % i) == 0:return True; break   # check up to sqrt(n), but give up early on a composite number 
        
def prime_numbers():     
    primes = [] # empty list for primes  
            
    for n in range(2, 101):       // loop through 2..100 (inclusive)
